The paper deals with foreground segmentation using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves feature fusion and end-to-end training, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also includes sample visualizations, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of deep neural networks and training with few examples suggests a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
